notesStmt.note: Imperfect at the beginning and at the end.
Several leaves inlaid with tracing paper for preservation.
Folios [i recto], 357r, 357v contain a fragment of Maimonides' Commentary on the Mishnah Midot 2:4-3:1.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Midrash ha-ḥefets, a philosophical midrash on the Pentateuch by Zechariah ben Solomon-Rofe, aka Yaḥya ben Saliman.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 27; written lines: 27; Titles of chapters and beginning of sections highlighted with red ink. Catchwords on every verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite semi-cursive script of 15 to 16th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine title: 'Midrash Ha-Chefets. Hebrew and Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2351.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 28 May 1881, inscribed, folio [358v].
